songs.lyrics:
I swung the election friends, that's no small order
I just blow notes and keep all the votes, from Canada to the Mexican border
I started out with a bang, below the Dixie line
Molten shot was burning hot, and every single vote was mine

From there I swung westward, taking every state in my stride
My bandwagon swinging, everybody started in to ride
I won every town and state, without exception
My friend, I swung the election

From there I swung westward, taking every state in my stride
My bandwagon swinging, and everybody started in to ride
I won every town and state, without exception
My friend, my friend, I swung the election

songs.lyrics:
I saw a peaceful old valley
With a carpet of corn for a floor
And I heard a voice within me whisper
This is worth fighting for

I saw a little old cabin
And the river that flowed by the door
And I heard a voice within me whisper
This is worth fighting for

Didn't I build that cabin?
Didn't I plant that corn?
Didn't my folks before me
Fight for this country before I was born?

I gathered my loved ones around me
And I gazed at each face I adore
Then I heard that voice within me thunder
This is worth fighting for

songs.lyrics:
You can boast about your riches, your every wish someone's command
You can go 'round cheatin' people, by some trickery or plan
You can tell lies on your neighbor, and think no one will ever know
But just as sure as you are living, you got to reap just what you sow

You've got to reap what you sow
Yes, you've got to reap what you sow
Oh, on the mountain in the valley
You've got to reap just what you sow

You can inconvenience others, to make things easy for yourself
You can steal some poor man's idea, and accumulate great wealth
But here's one thing that will happen, it’s been tried and proved before
All the wrong that you are doing, you got to reap just what you sow

You've got to reap what you sow
Yes, you've got to reap what you sow
Oh, on the mountain in the valley
You've got to reap just what you sow

You can take every advantage of a fellow man that is down
You can take somebody's heartstring, and drag it on the ground
You can high-hat other people, just because you are having luck
Even double-cross your best friend and then try and pass the buck
But there's one thing that will happen, makes no difference where you go
Just before your final curtain, you've got to reap just what you sow

You've got to reap what you sow
Yes, you've got to reap what you sow
Oh, on the mountain in the valley
You've got to reap just what you sow
